ownedComment.body: A single modeling environment for the specification of Enterprise Architecture Descriptions containing UML, SysML, BPMN, SoaML, and UPDM notations. Offers model simulation capabilities and rich extensibility via report scripting, tool macros, plugins, and APIs for Java, jRuby, Groovy, Javascript, and jPython programmatic access.

Eclipse is a multi-language Integrated development environment (IDE) comprising a base workspace and an extensible plug-in system for customizing the environment. It is written mostly in Java. It can be used to develop applications in Java and, by means of various plug-ins, other programming languages including Ada, C, C++, COBOL, Fortran, Haskell, JavaScript, Perl, PHP, Python, R, Ruby (including Ruby on Rails framework), Scala, Clojure, Groovy, Scheme, and Erlang.

Chores_Profile:Assignable_Business_Requi.Text: Types of "Projects" to be performed during the Period of Performance, their milestone sets, and their estimated durations of calendar time SHALL be documented in the PV-1, PV-2, and PV-3 Project Views of the Program's UPDM Enterprise Architecture model.
